Why This Is Asked
Assesses practical partitioning, backpressure handling, and exactly-once vs at-least-once trade-offs in a multi-tenant KCNA setup.

Key Concepts
- Tenant-aware partitioning
- Sticky routing and backpressure
- Exactly-once vs at-least-once semantics
- Lease migration and graceful rebalance
- Observability and testing

Code Example
```javascript
function shardForTenant(tenantId, shards){
  let h = 0;
  for(let i = 0; i < tenantId.length; i++){
    h = (h * 31 + tenantId.charCodeAt(i)) | 0;
  }
  return Math.abs(h) % shards;
}
```

